<scenario>
The agent A provided the following violation scenario:Violation occurs when attrs[i].buffer (a const void*) is cast to a non-const pointer (lfs_block_t *) and used. In the LFS_TYPE_TAIL branch the code performs ((lfs_block_t*)attrs[i].buffer)[0] and [1], discarding the const qualifier. This discarding of const violates MISRA C 2023 Rule 8.13 (pointer should point to const-qualified type whenever possible and not discard const).
</scenario>
